Description: Egypt, adult male "warrior" wearing cloth, trousers, neck-ornament [amulet?] and bead necklace. Holding stick in each hand. Street setting with European [?] wall and gate in background. Medium: Black and white. Gelatin silver print. Format: Print mounted on card.
Producer name: Photographed by: Captain Tristram C S Speedy
Curator's comments: Main Themes of Box: Rural life in Sudan, Ethiopia and Somaliland, including shelters, boat, shrine; paintings on exterior wall of a shelter; aerial photographs of a settlement; portraits of Somali chief and warrior. Warrior is Arab nomad. Suggested by E Kurimoto, (NME, Osaka) 31/01/1996. Geography: European ethnic group suggested by T Cotterill, 20/11/1996. Arab ethnic group suggested by E Kurimoto, (NME, Osaka), 31/01/1996. Circumstances: [KUR-] PIC DOC 09.
